@matthiasc, my idea was to make an application with tabs, but not to share actions between tabs, something like this (it's container hierarchy): 
```
Window-->Stack-->Tab1->Appmenu, Switcher, TabMenu & other widgets
              \->Tab2->Appmenu, Switcher, TabMenu & other widgets
```

Tabs themself implement GActionGroup & GActionMap. I chose this way, because I didn't find a way to add custom tab-specific Actions to a GtkMenu outside of this tab. I'd be glad to know, if there is a way to do that.

